If we want a remainder use the modulus symbol (%).
If we want to increase the same number then write (a = a+2).
If we want to increase the number by 1 then write(a++).
If we want to decrement the number by 1 then write(a--).
Note:
Here in java number++ ; ----------> POST-INCREMENT.
             ++number ; ----------> Pre-increment.
EXAMPLE:
class Main{
public static void main(String[]args){
int a = 8;
int a1 = a + 2;
int a2 = a++;
int a3 = ++a;
System.out.println(a1);     //incremented by 2
System.out.println(a2);    // it fetch the value and then increment
System.out.println(a3);    // it will first inrement and then fetch the value
}}

OUTPUT:
10
8
9
